        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 8:19PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 818 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Geraldine, or 25 miles southeast of Fort Benton, moving northeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Geraldine and Square Butte.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
